<h1 class="gap" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 36px; margin-top: 50px !important; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.1; color: inherit;">0x0A. Configuration management</h1>
<p><br></p>
<h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: aktiv-grotesk, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 30px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Background Context</h2>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: aktiv-grotesk, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><a href="https://youtu.be/ogYLFyp68cI" style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(148, 0, 40); text-decoration: underline; outline: -webkit-focus-ring-color auto 5px; outline-offset: -2px;" target="_blank"><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;"></a></p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id="isPasted" style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 0px; color: rgb(93, 111, 122); font-size: 48px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; font-family: marketing-sans, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(245, 248, 250); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The benefits of Puppet&rsquo;s declarative language</h2>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: marketing-sans, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(245, 248, 250); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; font-weight: bolder;">The Puppet DSL is tested.</strong> Thousands of people use Puppet modules, and they have, in effect, tested them for you. If you write a unique script, it has just one user &mdash; you. So you&rsquo;re the person responsible for checking whether it works, catching and fixing every error.</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: marketing-sans, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(245, 248, 250); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; font-weight: bolder;">It&rsquo;s repeatable.</strong> Once you run Puppet, you know the computer will be configured as it should be, in the state you&rsquo;ve defined. And you can use a manifest to configure as many machines as you need, even on multiple platforms.</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: marketing-sans, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(245, 248, 250); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; font-weight: bolder;">Consistency.</strong> No matter what state your servers start in, once you run Puppet, they&rsquo;ll end up exactly as you described. If you update your Puppet Apache module, every Apache machine managed by Puppet will update to the new configuration automatically. Your systems will throw fewer errors, and you&rsquo;ll swear less.</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: marketing-sans, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(245, 248, 250); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; font-weight: bolder;">You save time.</strong> It&rsquo;s much faster to run Puppet than to write a script. If a machine is accidentally configured incorrectly, Puppet will find the change and remediate it (unless you run Puppet in no-op mode, which is certainly an option).</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: marketing-sans, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(245, 248, 250); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; font-weight: bolder;">Self-documentation.</strong> Puppet manifests are so simple, anyone can read and understand them, including people outside your IT and engineering departments.<br style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important;"><img src="https://puppet.com/sites/default/files/styles/image_full_960_/public/images/blog/Puppet_Declarative_Language_vs_Procedural_Language.png?itok=p82FSldT" alt="Comparison of Puppet's declarative language with a procedural language" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; height: auto; max-width: 100%; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; font-weight: bolder;">Auditability.</strong> Many regulatory bodies accept Puppet manifests as proof of compliance. Whether it&rsquo;s an external or internal audit, it&rsquo;s great to have proof that you pass. And you can easily validate to your own executives that compliance requirements have been met.</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: marketing-sans, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(245, 248, 250); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Puppet&rsquo;s declarative language allows you to communicate the expected, desired state, not only to Puppet, but to the other humans on your team. It&rsquo;s easy for you to write, and easy for others to read and understand...even your boss.</p>
